      "content": "I hear you, but it's not a matter of guessing. Warfarin's effectiveness and safety are closely monitored through regular blood tests to ensure your INR (International Normalized Ratio) stays within the therapeutic range. Reducing your dose without these checks could be dangerous. Trust the process, and your doctor will adjust your treatment as needed based on your latest results. Your safety is the priority.",
      "source": "target",
